prompts.text: This is stage c, the model generates a low resolution latent, the default compression of 42 means that the width and height of the stage c latent are 1024 divided by 42.
This is stage b where the low resolution stage c latent is passed to the stage b model as conditioning. Stage b takes the low resolution latent and upscales it to a higher resolution one.
Stage a is what the VAE is called. It decodes the stage b latent into pixel space.
